{
  "texts": [
    "A similar effect was observed for mammogram screening adherence in the same area [8].",
    "The MUSC network might not be representative of the general population, but the same finding was reported by at least one more study in Pennsylvania [42].",
    "At the same time, this comes at odds with nationwide research that shows racial and ethnic minorities, including African Americans, are less likely to receive CRC screening compared to non-Hispanic Whites [45].",
    "One more study indicated that there are variations in adherence to screening tests based on race and ethnicity, with white participants showing a preference for colonoscopy, while non-white participants tend to prefer fecal testing [46].",
    "This preference difference highlights the importance of considering cultural factors and individual preferences when promoting screening adherence among diverse populations.Women had higher adherence to cancer screening in our population."
  ]
}